dcterms:description: The Objectworld environment is a grid-based simulation where an agent can choose between various actions, with stochastic transitions affecting its movement. It is used to evaluate inverse reinforcement learning algorithms by comparing learned policies against expert trajectories.
dcterms:title: Objectworld benchmark

dcterms:creator: Daniel Krajzewicz
Jakob Erdmann
Michael Behrisch
Laura Bieker-Walz
dcterms:description: SUMO is an open-source traffic simulation platform that allows for the modeling of urban mobility scenarios. It is used to evaluate the performance of autonomous driving algorithms by simulating lane-change behaviors under various constraints.
dcterms:title: SUMO (Simulation of Urban Mobility)
